gomodel:SYNGO_2825  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099061 replaced by GO:0098839" , "Rationale: Fig.4: \"At the electron-microscopic level, immunoreactivity for both calsyntenin-2 and -3 was most prominent in the postsynaptic specializations of asymmetric (Type I) synapses with both axodendritic and axospinous localization (Figs. 4E-4G and 5E-5H). Sections through the proximal dendrites revealed also strong immunolabeling of some internal membraneous organelles (Fig. 4G). In sections through the neuronal somas, calsyntenin-2 and -3 immunoreactivity was also found on the membranes of the endoplasmic reticulum and the Golgi apparatus. Occasionally, patchy staining of the somal and dendritic plasmamembrane was found (not shown).\"\n\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: - \"Immunolocalization of calsyntenin-2. Calsyntenin-2 was visualized in somatosensory (A) and cerebellar cortex (C) of adult mouse brain\nusing preembedding...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2825" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

